 of his life.","number":3}],"sources":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[{"type":"parallel_careers","related_id":"HD1170","display_label":"amassed a Gilded Age art collection rivaling Winthrop's"},{"type":"parallel_careers","related_id":"HD6608","link_text":"John Phillips Coolidge","display_label":"directed the Fogg Museum that received this collector’s gift"}],"quotes":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"statues":[],"bio":{"first_name":"Grenville Lindall","last_name":"Winthrop","display_name":"Grenville Lindall Winthrop","gender":"male","bio_blurb":"Art collector; bequeathed his collection to Harvard","photo_url":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dc5clrqtw/image/upload/v1780942517/8876342_b0cc4d73-c1e7-4c2d-be40-d4fce72ad1a4_lsm1up.jpg"},"military_service":[],"career":[],"birth":{"year":1864,"country":"United States","city":"New York","state":"New York"},"death":{"year":1943,"country":"United States","city":"New York","state":"New York"},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM582"},"education":[],"videos":[{"video_id":"VID017"}],"slug":"grenville-lindall-winthrop-1864"},"HD6045":{"id":"HD6045","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"gender":"male","classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"is_easter_egg":false,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"generation_from_thomas":11},"notable":{"is_notable":true,"notable_category":["arts"],"notable_blurb":"Sculptor, collector, and Audubon Sharon benefactor","primary_url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emily_Winthrop_Miles","primary_url_label":"Wikipedia"},"parents":{"father_id":"I01635","mother_id":"HD6042"},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"spouse_id":"I01636","children_ids":[],"marriage_number":1}],"tags":["artist"],"narrative_blocks":[{"category":"arts","header":"Sculptor who studied with Daniel Chester French","body":"Miles trained under Daniel Chester French and leading women sculptors of the day, and worked also as a painter, poet, and photographer. Her sculpture entered the Metropolitan, Montclair, and Harvard's Fogg collections.","number":1},{"category":"character","header":"She eloped with her father's chauffeur","body":"In 1924 the heiress eloped with Corey Miles, the widowed estate chauffeur, in a double wedding alongside her sister Kate. Their father Grenville was reportedly bitter for years over the matches.","number":2},{"category":"legacy","header":"Her glass and ceramics went to Brooklyn","body":"An avid collector, Miles left some 948 pieces of eighteenth-century Wedgwood, glass, and ceramics to the Brooklyn Museum. She also endowed the Emily Winthrop Miles wildlife sanctuary at Audubon Sharon.","number":3}],"sources":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[{"artwork_id":"ART083","role":"creator"}],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"quotes":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"statues":[],"bio":{"first_name":"Emily Lindall","last_name":"Winthrop","display_name":"Emily Lindall Winthrop Miles","gender":"female","married_names":["Miles"],"maiden_name":"Winthrop","bio_blurb":"Sculptor, collector, and Audubon Sharon benefactor","photo_url":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dc5clrqtw/image/upload/v1780942951/105427767_91fc0a9e-3b4b-46c8-bdf1-9eb24292d3e6_k7qkee.png"},"military_service":[],"career":[],"birth":{"year":1893,"country":"United States","city":"New York","state":"New York"},"death":{"year":1962,"country":"United States","city":"New York","state":"New York"},"burial":{},"education":[],"slug":"emily-lindall-winthrop-1893"},"I01636":{"id":"I01636","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"gender":"male","classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"include_in_path_calculation":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"par